Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.47,0:00:23.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\3c&H868203&}Today's deduction will take place in Sakurajima!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.27,0:00:24.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\3c&H868203&}While the battle over sake might have a sad ending...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.98,0:00:26.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\3c&H868203&}Uncle will solve this case even if he's drunk!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.14,0:00:28.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\3c&H868203&}Seeing through to the one and only truth...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.60,0:00:30.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\3c&H868203&}I look tike a child, but have the intellect of an adult.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.40,0:00:32.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\3c&H868203&}My name is Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.63,0:02:00.80,Giris,,0,0,0,,We traveled to Kagoshîma with Uncle Kogoro...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.80,0:02:04.18,Giris,,0,0,0,,There we visited the Takakuma Brewery,\Nhome of the famous, but rare, Shochu.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.35,0:02:11.94,Giris,,0,0,0,,While the company presidents wife,\NShiraishi Fumiko{\rHonorifics - Giris}-san{\r}, took us on an enjoyable tour...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.94,0:02:13.36,Giris,,0,0,0,,An incident occurred.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.15,0:02:19.69,Giris,,0,0,0,,Someone attacked and kidnapped the\Nmanaging director, Tatsumura Shinsukesan.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.07,0:02:21.45,Giris,,0,0,0,,And then...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.16,0:02:24.16,Giris,,0,0,0,,His body was discovered.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.16,0:02:27.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What? The murderer is one of us?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.16,0:02:30.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no doubt about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.87,0:02:35.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The only ones who knew Tatsumura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}\Nwell are those involved with this brewery.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.71,0:02:38.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I feel sorry for the wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.75,0:02:41.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Everyone close to her is under suspicion.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.26,0:02:46.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That may be true, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.18,0:02:47.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They're here!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.64,0:02:50.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit is most likely still here in this room.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.93,0:02:58.56,Signs,,0,0,0,,\N(Part 2)
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.93,0:02:58.56,Signs,,0,0,0,,Kogoro Gets Drunk in Satsuma
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.40,0:03:05.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How did things go?\NDid you get any useful Information?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.78,0:03:07.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.28,0:03:10.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They all have a motive and a shaky alibi, if any.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.45,0:03:12.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There aren't even any leads to follow.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.03,0:03:15.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's not true. There are two.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.99,0:03:21.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why did the culprit bother carrying Tatsumura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}s\Nbody out of his home and taking him somewhere else?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.16,0:03:26.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And why did they call two days\Nlater to tell us where the body was?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.42,0:03:28.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If we figure out these two mysteries
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.96,0:03:30.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.46,0:03:33.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's what he gets for pointing out such obvious things.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.09,0:03:35.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it s so obvıous then hurry up and figure it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.43,0:03:42.30,Signs,,0,0,0,,Shirashi Satoshi (30)\NTakakuma Brewery Owner
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.93,0:03:40.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, will you be questioning us again tomorrow?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.39,0:03:42.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, tomorrow morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.18,0:03:44.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're welcome to spend the night at our place.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.10,0:03:48.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maezono{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} will be staying as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.23,0:03:50.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, that would be a bıg help! Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.44,0:03:51.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, then...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.81,0:03:53.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't think he's the«murderer.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.94,0:03:57.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Would a murderer invite a detective to stay at his house?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.15,0:04:00.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The most suspicious ones are usually\Nthe most unnaturally innocent-looking.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.49,0:04:02.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Jeez, you're so untrusting.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.57,0:04:08.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, I shouldn't be laughing
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.92,0:04:17.42,Giris,,0,0,0,,The two mysteries...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.67,0:04:21.88,Giris,,0,0,0,,There must be something that can piece them together
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.88,0:04:22.96,Giris,,0,0,0,,There has îo be...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.68,0:04:26.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Good morning!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.80,0:04:27.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, good morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.34,0:04:31.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,it looks like everyone's already busy workıng.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.43,0:04:32.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.97,0:04:35.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The brewing process sure start s early, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.98,0:04:39.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Our staff wakes up at 4:30 AM and starts working at 5:00.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.94,0:04:42.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,İt sounds like really hard work.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.52,0:04:45.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sake is fılled with living organisms.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.19,0:04:49.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Once you start making it, you can't\Ntake your eyes off of it for a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.74,0:04:53.49,Signs,,0,0,0,,Shiraishi Fumiko (27)\NSatoshi Wife
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.74,0:04:53.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why none of us could have left during that time.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.12,0:04:55.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess that's true?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.16,0:04:58.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah! I came to call you for breakfast.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.70,0:04:59.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Özür dileriz.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.37,0:05:01.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come in whenever you re ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.33,0:05:06.75,Giris,,0,0,0,,They loved their sake so much that\Nthey wouldn't have left the brewery.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.75,0:05:08.54,Giris,,0,0,0,,If that's true..
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.84,0:05:13.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dad?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.26,0:05:18.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's with the creepy laugh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.05,0:05:19.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Realty?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.89,0:05:21.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The murderer is...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.89,0:05:23.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maezono Hitomi.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.89,0:05:27.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why do you think it's her?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.35,0:05:31.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She's the only female suspect.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.90,0:05:34.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The first mystery/
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.82,0:05:38.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why did she move he body out of the house?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.74,0:05:41.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tatsumura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was a tall, fit man.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.66,0:05:45.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No one would expect a woman to\Nhave enough strength to carry him.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.87,0:05:48.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She's a woman, therefore she couldn't be the culprit!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.62,0:05:52.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is what she wanted everyone to think.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.46,0:05:54.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What about the second mystery?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.79,0:05:57.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why did she tell us where the body was?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.79,0:05:59.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's obvious.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.30,0:06:04.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She wanted memorial services to be held for him,\Nconcerned that his soul would be unable to rest in peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.88,0:06:06.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That feminine way of thinking...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.55,0:06:09.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Means the culprit has to be Maezono Hitomi.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.56,0:06:14.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,hope Officer Shinpuku hurries up...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.98,0:06:17.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I want him to hear my perfect deduction.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.44,0:06:18.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, Uncle...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.39,0:06:18.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.15,0:06:21.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's impossible for a woman to\Nhave committed the crime, right
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.19,0:06:23.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How was Maezono{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} able to do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.77,0:06:27.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it's impossible, then I guess it's impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.49,0:06:28.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.90,0:06:33.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maezono Hitomi ıs secretly a\Nheavyweight-class body builder
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.53,0:06:35.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She probably lifts weights or something like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.78,0:06:36.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.37,0:06:37.62,Giris,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey..
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.79,0:06:41.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, go take a quick peek inside her room.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.66,0:06:42.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.66,0:06:46.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She probably has a very muscular body.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.58,0:06:49.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,İt's okay if you peep because you're still a kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.96,0:06:52.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no way I'm doing that!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.26,0:06:55.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey! Help me out for once!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.13,0:06:57.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why are you asking a child to spy on a naked woman?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.68,0:07:00.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, this is purely for investigative purposes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.31,0:07:03.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Give me a break
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.81,0:07:10.10,Signs,,0,0,0,,Orita Seiichi (60)\NTakakuma Brewery Employee
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.81,0:07:08.94,Üstyazı,,0,0,0,,Just so you know, I'm not skıpping work or anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.94,0:07:12.73,Üstyazı,,0,0,0,,It's just that I'm old now,\Nand my back and neck are always aching.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.40,0:07:16.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I remember back in my day...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.40,0:07:21.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah! Is that you?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.45,0:07:23.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was taken 20 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.03,0:07:28.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's Tatsumura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, and the one in the center\Nıs the former president who passed away last year.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.04,0:07:30.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eh? Who are these kids?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.29,0:07:34.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The current president.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.88,0:07:36.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not his little sıster. That's Fumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.88,0:07:38.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She s the president s wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.71,0:07:40.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, they're childhood friends?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.84,0:07:44.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And that's her father, standing beside me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.30,0:07:47.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,used to work here with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.22,0:07:56.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The predecessor only had one son.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.56,0:08:00.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So he treated Fumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r} like she\Nwas his own cute little daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.36,0:08:05.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Fumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}'s father was also an excellent sake brewer.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.48,0:08:10.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But tragedy struck when he fell ili and\Npassed away while she was ın middle school.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.28,0:08:16.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, the predecessor\Ndidn't ignore his remaining family.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.24,0:08:19.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He gave her encouragement and supported her financially...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.29,0:08:21.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even paying for her high school tuition.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.79,0:08:24.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He also helped her get into nursing school.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.75,0:08:28.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She really owes a lot to the former president, doesn't she?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.84,0:08:30.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, by the way...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.96,0:08:32.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Excuse me, ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.59,0:08:36.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,re you the nurse who used to work at the Chuo Hospital?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.01,0:08:39.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. That was five years ago, before I got married.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.14,0:08:42.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She was a nurse, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.43,0:08:47.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, that's why she scheduled an appoıntment\Nfor the managing director to visit the hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.98,0:08:50.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A physical checkup.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.81,0:08:53.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah... I remember him saying something about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.82,0:08:56.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry, sorry. I'm late for your interview.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.48,0:09:02.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\3c&H525254&}My physical checkup took longer than\NI expected thanks to a certain someone
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.28,0:09:07.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If she had known he would have died the next day,\NFumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r} probably wouldn't have recommended it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.54,0:09:11.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eh? The mistress recommended that\NTatsumura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} get the physical checkup?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.41,0:09:17.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He used to have a physical checkup done annually,\Nbut he's been busy as the managing director as of late.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.34,0:09:20.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, the mistress was really\Npushing him to get one this year.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.38,0:09:23.38,Giris,,0,0,0,,And he was murderered the next day.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.38,0:09:25.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Physıcal checkup?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.01,0:09:26.93,Giris,,0,0,0,,C-Could that....?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.30,0:09:28.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is somethıng wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.64,0:09:30.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, it's nothıng.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.26,0:09:32.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, I guess I better get back to work.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.76,0:09:36.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I have to get things done before\Nthe police start questıoning me agaın.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.68,0:09:37.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See you later, young man.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.40,0:09:41.90,Giris,,0,0,0,,Things a re almost wrapped up.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.90,0:09:42.81,Giris,,0,0,0,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.82,0:09:46.65,Giris,,0,0,0,,if they used that trick, then the\Ntwo mysteries are already resolved.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.36,0:09:48.99,Giris,,0,0,0,,But there's no evidence..
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.57,0:09:51.99,Giris,,0,0,0,,Sakurajima?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.36,0:09:53.91,Giris,,0,0,0,,Waıt a mınute back then...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.91,0:09:54.99,Giris,,0,0,0,,That s it!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.62,0:09:57.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, Mourisan.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.20,0:10:00.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was just about to head there...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.58,0:10:01.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.21,0:10:03.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Before you leave, I have a favor to ask of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.37,0:10:07.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, I want you to examine Tatsumura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s body.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.96,0:10:10.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, I want to know if there was something on his clothes...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.18,0:10:16.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come on
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.89,0:10:19.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Show me them muscles, baby!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.22,0:10:20.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you looking at?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.85,0:10:22.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I saw Shinpuku{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.51,0:10:23.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.43,0:10:26.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Jeez...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.06,0:10:30.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I looked into,what you asked me,\Nand there wasn't even a trace on him.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.36,0:10:32.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What a re you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.77,0:10:36.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At last, the final piece falls into place.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.23,0:10:38.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But you just called and asked me to...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.69,0:10:41.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh my, Dad... You asked for something and forgot about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.16,0:10:44.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh! That thing, that thing!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.41,0:10:47.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see. There wasn't any on him, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.79,0:10:49.74,Giris,,0,0,0,,You're pretty good at fooling people.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.75,0:10:51.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, who is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.58,0:10:52.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.83,0:10:54.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Didn't you say that you knew on the phone?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.88,0:10:57.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And you said you'd reveal who\Nthe culprit was when we got here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.92,0:11:00.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, who ıs the culprit?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.80,0:11:03.13,Giris,,0,0,0,,I might have saıd that..
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.38,0:11:07.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, the culprit is... a woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.51,0:11:08.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maezono Hitomi!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.89,0:11:10.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.22,0:11:11.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And that is based on the fact that...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.18,0:11:12.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uncle!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.89,0:11:15.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you know who dıd it go and\N\in front of everyone and tell them.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.23,0:11:16.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Rıght.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.82,0:11:30.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We know that Tatsumura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s death was a murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.20,0:11:32.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But who is the murderer?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.91,0:11:35.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The murderer is...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.20,0:11:36.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wow! Look at Sakurajima!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.54,0:11:42.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is something happening on the mountain?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.37,0:11:43.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, i don't see anything strange...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.26,0:11:52.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, Shinpuku{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.67,0:11:53.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.34,0:11:58.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-This is the famous Sleeping Kogoro!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.60,0:12:02.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,www.Elzsubs.blogspot.com\NDiscort: ELz-FaN
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.52,0:12:08.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is it, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.56,0:12:09.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.48,0:12:11.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.44,0:12:16.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He probably thought the volcanoes on Sakurajima erupted.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.40,0:12:19.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Orita{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, this is the famous Sleeping Kogoro.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.99,0:12:22.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Excuse me, may I take a picture?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.32,0:12:23.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please, I need quiet.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.74,0:12:28.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit used an alibi trick to murder Tatsumura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.08,0:12:34.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Alibi trick?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.71,0:12:39.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I had a good idea about how the trick was done,\Nbut I needed to get some concrete evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.46,0:12:42.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, I asked for something.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.46,0:12:44.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\3c&H474751&}Ashes from Sakurajima?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.55,0:12:47.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, Id like to know if you find\Nany on Tsumura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s clothes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.72,0:12:51.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,İn the end, we couldn't find a\Nsingle trace of ash on his clothes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.47,0:12:56.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But when I happened to see Kagoshima's weather report...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.94,0:13:06.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,İt said that ashes would be falling continuously from\Nnoon to around midnight on the day Tatsumura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} died.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.57,0:13:10.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\3c&H5C5C61&}Hey, do you taste something weird in your mouth?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.99,0:13:13.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\3c&H59595E&}Now that you mention it...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.12,0:13:14.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\3c&H616165&}It's the volcano.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.20,0:13:16.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\3c&H616165&}It has to be all ashes
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.24,0:13:18.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, ashes were definitely falling like rain that day.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.79,0:13:20.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't it strange, then...?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.54,0:13:24.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We arrived at the house at six o'clock.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.25,0:13:29.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If Tatsumura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} had been murdered\Nand carried out side during that time...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.75,0:13:33.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then some of the airborne ash would have\Ngotten on the clothes he had been wearing.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.30,0:13:40.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, there was no trace of ashes on him.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.80,0:13:46.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which means Tatsumura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was not\Nattacked in the evening as we previously thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.18,0:13:50.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,İt happened in the morning, before the ash started falling.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.44,0:13:52.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.19,0:13:54.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But then...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.11,0:13:56.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, one thing doesn't match up.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.61,0:14:00.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,İt's blood!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.32,0:14:07.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now, I wonder how that blood got there, Madam?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.46,0:14:15.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,l made a slight error in my judgment earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.75,0:14:20.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why did you offer to take us on a\Nsightseeing tour of the area that day?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.17,0:14:27.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was it really just to get me to deny Tatsumura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s\Nrequest to advertise their brand...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.01,0:14:32.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\3c&H646468&}Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, please decline the offer from Tatsumura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.56,0:14:35.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\3c&H646468&}I thought that was the reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.18,0:14:37.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.73,0:14:40.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\3c&H717176&}We were just there to set up her alibi.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.69,0:14:44.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\3c&H717176&}İt was a setup to throw the investigation off...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.23,0:14:50.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\3c&H717176&}By making us believe that one of your\Nco workers had killed Tatsumura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue} san{\r} just before we arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.57,0:14:53.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that rıght, Madam?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.37,0:14:55.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-That can't be...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.74,0:14:59.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,M Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.12,0:15:02.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I told you the culprit was a woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.29,0:15:05.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So the woman was t
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.92,0:15:09.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,İt was Shıraısh Fumıkosan.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.51,0:15:21.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That morning, after offering to give us a tour...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.31,0:15:26.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\3c&H5B5B60&}Madam?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.39,0:15:29.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\3c&H535359&}Oh, Madam.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.81,0:15:35.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\3c&H65656B&}And then you told him you wanted to speak\Nto him in private so he'd get back in the car.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.86,0:15:37.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\3c&H65656B&}That's when you drugged him to sleep. I expect that...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.74,0:15:43.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\3c&H65656B&}Drawing blood from him was a simple task for you...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.28,0:15:46.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\3c&H65656B&}...as you had been in the nursing field for years.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.54,0:15:50.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\3c&H65656B&}Afterwards, you came to the hotel to pick us up.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.29,0:15:59.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\3c&H65656B&}You spent the entire day with us...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.09,0:16:03.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then took us to Tatsumura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s\Nhouse in order to make us your witnesses.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.80,0:16:05.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\3c&H646466&}It's open.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.18,0:16:07.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\3c&H646466&}I'II go look İnside.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.34,0:16:09.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\3c&H646466&}Tasumura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.51,0:16:10.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\3c&H646466&}It's Shirashi.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.10,0:16:16.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then you went to the living room to carry out your plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.07,0:16:26.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\3c&H525256&}Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.03,0:16:27.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\3c&H525256&}Madam!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.49,0:16:29.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\3c&H525256&}What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.15,0:16:32.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The first of the two mysteries was...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.61,0:16:35.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why did the culprit carry the body out of the house?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.53,0:16:38.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The answer to that is actually quite simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.04,0:16:41.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The body was never ın the house from the start.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.16,0:16:44.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why were the lights on?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.21,0:16:53.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Before she picked us up, she used Tatsumura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s\Nhouse key, which she stole after she put him to sleep...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.01,0:16:59.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To enter his house, turn on the lights,\Nand then leave with the front door remaining unlocked.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.85,0:17:02.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So that's how it happened...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.22,0:17:04.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait a minute!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.43,0:17:07.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Regarding the second mystery .
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.14,0:17:08.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I told you to wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.81,0:17:13.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There s something that doesn't sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.02,0:17:14.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I just don't get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.94,0:17:20.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're accusing Fumiko of the murder,\Nbut wasn't she with you the whole day?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.53,0:17:23.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She couldn't have done it!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.32,0:17:26.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When did she have have the opportunity to do all that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.29,0:17:31.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That s right, Dad. When did she?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.58,0:17:34.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,İt was after that, wasn't it, Madam?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.05,0:17:42.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\3c&H57575A&}I apologize for involving you in such trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.63,0:17:47.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,İt was after she dropped us off at the hotel.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.98,0:18:06.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You had a sculpture prepared which was\Nexactly like the one that Tatsumura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} owned.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.08,0:18:28.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,İn short, this murder case occurred only\Nafter the police had started investigating.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.80,0:18:32.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was our blind spot.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.09,0:18:33.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't blame you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.47,0:18:37.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No one would think to check alibis for\Nwhere someone was during the investigation
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.76,0:18:45.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You made us thınk Tatsumura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue} san{\r} was\Nmurdered just before we arrived at his house.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.43,0:18:49.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because of that, you were able\Nto create a seemingly airtight alibı.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.19,0:18:53.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After all, you were with us the entire day.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.44,0:18:55.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As or the second mystery...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.15,0:18:59.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why did the culprit tell us\Nwhere the body was two days later?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.15,0:19:03.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\3c&H616164&}While it's hard to determine the\Ntime of death accurately after two days...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.66,0:19:06.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\3c&H515155&}We believe he was killed sometime\Nduring the evening he went missing.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.91,0:19:12.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If the body was discovered immediately,\Ninvestigators would be able to pinpoint the time of death.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.29,0:19:15.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If too much time passed, the estimated\Ntime of death wouldn't be specific enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.33,0:19:23.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Either one of those scenarios would render her alibi useless.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.88,0:19:28.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, when and why did you start to suspect me?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.43,0:19:33.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On the day before he died, didn't you\Nrecommend that Tatsumura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} get a physical checkup?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.93,0:19:35.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, şey...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.18,0:19:37.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What does that have to do with it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.64,0:19:41.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Having an injection from a syringe\Nmakes a small prick mark<appear on your arm.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.65,0:19:44.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The same mark would be there after having blood drawn.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.82,0:19:51.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She knew no one would question the prick mark's presence\Nif he had had a physical checkup done the day before.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.86,0:19:56.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Basıcally, you carefully injected the syringe in\Nthe same spot he already had his blood drawn from.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.66,0:19:58.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.91,0:20:00.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.79,0:20:02.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why did you kill Tatsumura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.75,0:20:05.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was scared.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.96,0:20:08.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought that if Tatsumura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} continued to work here...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.92,0:20:16.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,People would start to care more about\Nmaking money than about the quality of the sake.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.68,0:20:20.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I didn't want people to start thinking that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.14,0:20:24.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No Madam! None of us are like that)
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.27,0:20:30.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For now, but time can{\rHonorifics - Dialogue} chan{\r}ge a person.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.02,0:20:32.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just like Tatsumura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.06,0:20:33.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just like he{\rHonorifics - Dialogue} chan{\r}ged.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.98,0:20:36.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,İt s my fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.48,0:20:38.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If only I had fired Tatsumura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} before this happened...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.07,0:20:43.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You a re unwilling to fire\Npeople to whom you a re indebted to.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.03,0:20:44.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I like that side of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.24,0:20:48.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, what drove you to do suchia thing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.45,0:20:51.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wanted to be remembered.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.16,0:20:55.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wanted to be remembered as\Nthe one who protected this brewery.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.63,0:21:00.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course, murder is an unforgivable crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.00,0:21:06.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But she felt she had to protect the brewery\Nin order to repay the predecessor's kindness.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.59,0:21:08.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My father...?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.10,0:21:11.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You could never forget a favor.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.26,0:21:13.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since your wife is also from Satsuma...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.43,0:21:15.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I believe that she shares the same sentiments that you do.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.19,0:21:21.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Fumiko...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.02,0:21:24.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course we feel the same way.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.78,0:21:27.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's my beloved husband.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.62,0:21:40.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't bother with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.91,0:21:42.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You need hurry and get back to work!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.21,0:21:44.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Madam...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.92,0:21:46.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Fumiko.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.33,0:21:50.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There a re people all over Japan waiting for you r sake.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.51,0:21:52.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And I II be waiting for you...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.67,0:21:56.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because just like our sake\Nmy feelings for you a re the real thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.47,0:22:02.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And so, yet another case was solved.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.39,0:22:14.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Bunu fark ettiğimde, nostaljik\Nbiri olmak zorunda kaldım.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.90,0:22:23.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Rüyanın devamı öngören dünlerimiz vardı.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.12,0:22:30.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,O gün çok büyümüş gibiydi...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.75,0:22:36.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Veda bile edemeden, şemsiyemin altına sakladım.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.92,0:22:42.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eğer yolları tekrar geçersek... Lütfen...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.63,0:22:45.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,O zaman, unutma beni.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.13,0:22:55.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Değişmeyecek aşk gibi değil sevgi gibi değil...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.39,0:23:06.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Her zaman olacağını düşünüyorum,\Nsadece seni seviyorum ve bu...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.24,0:23:16.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Amaçsız duygularımı tutarak, insanların\Nsık sık yaptığı gibi geriye bakıyorum.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.99,0:23:29.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sahneyi durdur, yavaşça\Nkaybolmadan buluşmak bizim tek şansımız.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.51,0:23:39.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Off, Takakuma isn't here after all...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.10,0:23:39.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Takakuma, Takakuma...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.39,0:23:42.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, screw this! I don t care what I get!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.31,0:23:47.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're still going to buy more?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.64,0:23:50.98,Giris,,0,0,0,,So you re goıng with quantıty over quality, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.98,0:23:54.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Black vinegar is really good for you!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.94,0:23:58.03,Giris,,0,0,0,,Like father, like daughter
